On the evening of March 11, the World Health Organization said the new pneumonia outbreak "has acquired the characteristics of a global pandemic" . On the morning of March 12, Tom Hanks and his wife became the first Hollywood stars to be diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia.

The US film star Tom Hanks and his wife said in a statement today that they had tested positive for new coronary pneumonia. The Tom Hanks said on Twitter that they had been diagnosed with new pneumonia while filming a new film in Australia. "We feel a little tired, like we have a cold and some body aches. Rita has some chills and some mild fever. " The Tom Hanks said it would be under quarantine, and update the situation in a timely manner, and I hope you take good care of yourself.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Tom Hanks

The epidemic has spread around the world, affecting Hollywood's film and Television Industry.

Some of the crew have already stopped filming. According to deadline10 March, shooting of the czech-based Marvel Series Falcon and winter soldier has been halted due to a new crown disease. Filming for the show was originally scheduled for a week in the Czech capital Prague, but Disney pulled the plug after the Czech government cancelled film screenings, school classes, sports and cultural events due to the new crown disease. The Prague cast of "the Falcon and the winter soldier" has been recalled to its main location in Atlanta, USA, and deadline doesn't think there's much chance of a return to Prague. The show was originally scheduled to hit Disney + in August.

A series of film and television events had to be postponed. On March 8, Bob Gazzale, CEO and president of AFI, the Film Society of America, announced that the AFI 48th annual lifetime achievement awards dinner scheduled for April 25 would be postponed until early summer, pending official announcement.

SXSW Film Festival cancelled due to outbreak. On March 6, South by southwest (SXSW) announced through its official twitter that the 2020 SXSW Film Festival had been canceled due to the new pneumonia outbreak in the United States. Earlier, apple, Amazon, Netflix and many other exhibitors announced the cancellation of this year's south by southwest film festival screening plans. In Texas, home of the South by Southwest Film Festival, 17 cases have been confirmed.

But there are still pockets and agencies that are holding out under the epidemic.

In the face of the COVID-19 outbreak, France announced a ban on large public gatherings of 5,000 people or more and extended the ban until the end of May. But the Cannes Film Festival, which opens on May 12th, says it will go ahead. The Cannes Film Festival rejected an offer by the Insurance Company Circle Group to buy an option on an epidemic 10 days ago if a government order cancels it in the future because of a new crown disease, Cannes Film Festival reported, is Not covered by the insurance.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The cast of Mulan Premieres in the United States, photo: Visual China

The Disney Live Action Film Mulan, starring Liu Yifei, premiered at the Dolby Theatre in 2008 East West Bank Classic – Doubles yesterday. The Film Stars Liu Yifei, Donnie Yen, Jet Li, and an Yousen all appeared on the red carpet. Although the outbreak in the United States has not yet been brought under control, Disney has insisted that Mulan be released in North America on March 27.

The confirmation of the Tom Hanks may make the world's film and Television Industry Take the issue seriously. After all, being alive is all that matters.
